Training data models and simulations on a local computer can be beneficial for various reasons. Firstly, it offers more control over the hardware environment, allowing users to optimize configurations for specific tasks, potentially improving performance. Local setups also eliminate concerns about internet connectivity affecting training speeds or interruptions.

Moreover, privacy and security considerations may make local training preferable for sensitive data, as it avoids transmitting information over the internet. Cost efficiency is another factor, as running large-scale computations in the cloud can accumulate expenses, while local setups may incur lower or one-time costs.

However, cloud platforms offer scalability advantages, enabling users to access substantial computing power on demand. The choice between local and cloud-based training often depends on specific requirements, resources, and the nature of the project.